mages and provides a critical analysis of the role historical museums play in the contemporary world. As the catastrophes of World War II still exert an enormous influence on the national identities of Russians, Poles, and Germans, museum exhibits can thus play an important role in this process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCollective memoryzEurope, Eastern. 0aDeutsche. 0aErinnerungskultur. 0aGeschichtsbild. 0aGeschichtspolitik. 0aIdentität. 0aMemorializationzEurope, Eastern. 0aMuseum exhibitsxEurope, Eastern. 0aMuseum. 0aOsteuropa. 0aPolen/Bevölkerung. 0aRussen. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xEurope, Eastern. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xInfluence. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMuseumsxEurope, Eastern. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMuseumszEurope, Eastern. 0aZweiter Weltkrieg. 70(DE-588)4040795-00(DE-627)1062214850(DE-576)209042311aMuseum2gnd 70(DE-588)4079167-10(DE-627)1060754030(DE-576)209211199aZweiter Weltkrieg2gnd 70(DE-588)4128844-00(DE-627)1057142590(DE-576)209605545aSammlung2gnd 70(DE-588)4129601-10(DE-627)1042794350(DE-576)209611855aAusstellung2gnd 70(DE-588)4200793-80(DE-627)1051709250(DE-576)210137975aKollektives Gedächtnis2gnd 70(DE-588)4281014-00(DE-627)1043721330(DE-576)210764309aMusealisierung2gnd 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh1 aBogumił, Zuzanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchen, Tim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWawrzyniak, Joanna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782382188?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782382188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/978178238